---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Our History">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-content">
      <h1>Our History</h1>
      <p>From humble beginnings to a thriving community of faith</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="timeline-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>A Journey of Faith</h2>
      <div class="decorative-line center"></div>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-year">1982</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h3>The Beginning</h3>
            <p>
              The Byzantine Catholic community of Dallas was begun as a mission, served by
              St. John Chrysostom Church in Houston. Divine Liturgies were celebrated weekly
              either at the University of Dallas or Holy Trinity Seminary.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-year">1985</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h3>Finding a Home</h3>
            <p>
              A handful of dedicated faithful decided there was a future for a Byzantine
              Catholic church in the Metroplex. After a long search, they courageously
              moved forward and purchased two acres of land with a four-bedroom house
              near Irving, chosen for its central location and accessibility.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-year">1988</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h3>Becoming a Parish</h3>
            <p>
              On March 27, 1988, the mission was officially declared a parish. Father Robert Karl,
              pastor of the Houston parish, was designated the first pastor-administrator of
              St. Basil the Great Church.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <div class="timeline-year">Oct 9, 1988</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h3>Church Dedication</h3>
            <p>
              Bishop John Bilock was present for the church dedication, along with the Roman
              Catholic Bishop of Dallas. The crowd was overflowing, and a festive dinner was
              held outdoors to celebrate this milestone.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-year">1989</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h3>Expansion</h3>
            <p>
              After several meetings and proposals, the community decided to add an extension
              to the chapel. In a creative solution, the existing swimming pool was converted
              into a floor for the new church, and a roof was constructed. The expanded church
              was rededicated on November 19, 1989.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <div class="timeline-year">1993</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h3>Iconography Completed</h3>
            <p>
              The iconography was completed, creating the beautiful church interior that
              parishioners and visitors admire today. The icons serve as "windows to heaven,"
              inviting all to contemplate the mysteries of our faith.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-year">Today</div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h3>A Growing Community</h3>
            <p>
              The parish continues to grow and thrive with many large families of children
              in attendance every week. Under the pastoral care of Fr. Elias Rafaj and
              the deacons, the faithful continue to worship in the ancient Byzantine
              tradition, welcoming all who seek to experience the beauty of Eastern Christianity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="patron-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="patron-content">
        <div class="patron-text">
          <h2>Our Patron: St. Basil the Great</h2>
          <div class="decorative-line"></div>
          <p class="dates">c. 330 – January 1, 379</p>
          <p>
            St. Basil the Great was the Bishop of Caesarea in Cappadocia (modern-day Turkey)
            and one of the most influential figures in the early Church. He is venerated as
            a Doctor of the Church in both East and West.
          </p>
          <p>
            Along with his brother St. Gregory of Nyssa and his friend St. Gregory the Theologian,
            he is counted among the "Three Great Hierarchs" and "Cappadocian Fathers." His
            contributions to theology, monasticism, and liturgy remain foundational to
            Christian practice today.
          </p>
          <h3>His Legacy</h3>
          <ul class="patron-legacy">
            <li>Authored the Divine Liturgy of St. Basil, still celebrated today</li>
            <li>Founded monasteries and wrote influential monastic rules</li>
            <li>Established hospitals and charitable institutions for the poor</li>
            <li>Defended the doctrine of the Holy Trinity against Arianism</li>
            <li>His feast is celebrated on January 1st</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="patron-quote">
          <blockquote>
            "A tree is known by its fruit; a man by his deeds. A good deed is never lost;
            he who sows courtesy reaps friendship, and he who plants kindness gathers love."
          </blockquote>
          <cite>— St. Basil the Great</cite>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="archeparchy-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Byzantine Catholic Archeparchy of Pittsburgh</h2>
      <div class="decorative-line center"></div>
      <div class="archeparchy-content">
        <p>
          St. Basil the Great is part of the Byzantine Catholic Archeparchy of Pittsburgh,
          which oversees Byzantine Catholic parishes in much of the central and eastern
          United States. The Archeparchy traces its roots to the Ruthenian immigrants
          who came to America in the late 19th and early 20th centuries, bringing
          their ancient faith with them.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Ruthenian Byzantine Catholic Church entered into communion with Rome
          through the Union of Uzhhorod in 1646, while maintaining its distinctive
          Eastern liturgical, spiritual, and theological traditions.
        </p>
        <div class="archeparchy-info">
          <div class="info-item">
            <h4>Established</h4>
            <p>1924</p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-item">
            <h4>Cathedral</h4>
            <p>St. John the Baptist, Munhall, PA</p>
          </div>
          <div class="info-item">
            <h4>Metropolitan</h4>
            <p>Archbishop William C. Skurla</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Be Part of Our Story</h2>
      <p>Join our community and become part of our continuing history.</p>
      <a href={`${base}contact`} class="btn btn-primary">Visit Us</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--burgundy-dark) 0%, var(--burgundy) 50%, var(--navy) 100%);
    padding: 8rem 2rem 6rem;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-light);
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 3.5rem);
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .page-hero p {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .decorative-line {
    width: 80px;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .decorative-line.center {
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .timeline-section {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    background: var(--cream);
  }

  .timeline-section h2 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    color: var(--burgundy);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .timeline {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 3rem auto 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 120px;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 3px;
    background: var(--gold);
  }

  .timeline-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 100px 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .timeline-item::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 112px;
    top: 8px;
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    background: var(--cream);
    border: 3px solid var(--gold);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .timeline-item.highlight::after {
    background: var(--gold);
  }

  .timeline-year {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--burgundy);
    text-align: right;
    padding-top: 5px;
  }

  .timeline-content {
    background: var(--white);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  }

  .timeline-item.highlight .timeline-content {
    border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
  }

  .timeline-content h3 {
    color: var(--navy);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .timeline-content p {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .patron-section {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    background: var(--white);
  }

  .patron-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .patron-text h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--burgundy);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .patron-text .dates {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--burgundy);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .patron-text p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .patron-text h3 {
    color: var(--navy);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .patron-legacy {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .patron-legacy li {
    padding: 0.6rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .patron-legacy li::before {
    content: '☦';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .patron-quote {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--burgundy) 0%, var(--burgundy-dark) 100%);
    padding: 3rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .patron-quote blockquote {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .patron-quote cite {
    color: var(--gold);
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
  }

  .archeparchy-section {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    background: var(--cream);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .archeparchy-section h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--burgundy);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .archeparchy-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .archeparchy-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .archeparchy-info {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    background: var(--white);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .info-item h4 {
    color: var(--gold);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .info-item p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--navy);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-section {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy) 0%, var(--navy-light) 100%);
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-light);
  }

  .cta-section h2 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cta-section p {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--gold);
    color: var(--navy);
    border: 2px solid var(--gold);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--gold-light);
    border-color: var(--gold-light);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .timeline::before {
      left: 20px;
    }

    .timeline-item {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      padding-left: 50px;
    }

    .timeline-item::after {
      left: 12px;
    }

    .timeline-year {
      text-align: left;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .patron-content {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .archeparchy-info {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
